# <%= current_page.data.title %>

All projects must align with the Cabinet Office Cyber Security policy. This policy defines the department-wide approach to security and assigns key roles and responsibilities.

### Compliance areas

The internal framework covers:

* Governance & Risk: how we manage and assure departmental security.  
* Asset & Data Security: protection of physical and digital information assets.  
* Operational Security: standards for networks, systems, and identity control.  
* Response & Recovery: procedures for vulnerability management and incident handling.  
  


### Information for external partners

The security policy framework is an internal document. Suppliers or contractors who need specific technical standards, such as the GitHub security standard or password standard, please access the link below via your provided internal credentials.

